ttyctl -fu
       The -f option freezes the tty, and -u unfreezes it.  When the tty is frozen, no changes made to the tty settings by ex
       honored by the shell, except for changes in the size of the screen; the shell will simply reset the settings to their 
       as  each  command  exits or is suspended.  Thus, stty and similar programs have no effect when the tty is frozen.  Wit
       whether the terminal is frozen or not.
